==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eld
<hw>Eld</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>yldu</ets>, <ets>yldo</ets>,
<ets>eldo</ets>, old age, fr. <ets>ald</ets>, <ets>eald</ets>, old. See
<er>Old</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Age; esp., old age.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As sooth is said, <qex>eelde</qex> hath great avantage.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Great Nature, ever young, yet full of <qex>eld</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Old times; former days; antiquity.</def>
<mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Astrologers and men of <qex>eld</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eld</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Eld
<hw>Eld</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To age; to grow old.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eld</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Eld
<hw>Eld</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make old or ancient.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Time, that <qex>eldeth</qex> all things.</q> <rj><qau>Rom. of
R.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

